# Utils Layer
#
# Contains shared utility classes and helpers:
#   ApiResponse.js   — Standardized response envelope factory
#                      ApiResponse.success(data, message, statusCode)
#                      ApiResponse.error(message, statusCode, errorCode)
#   ApiError.js      — Custom Error subclass with statusCode, errorCode, isOperational
#                      Subclasses: ValidationError, AuthenticationError,
#                                  NotFoundError, ConflictError
#   asyncHandler.js  — Wraps async route handlers to forward unhandled
#                      promise rejections to Express error middleware via next(err)
#
# Rule: Utils are pure, stateless, framework-agnostic helpers.
#       They must have zero side effects and zero external dependencies.
#
# Populated in: Milestone 10 (API Response Standardization)
#               Milestone 9  (Centralized Error Handling)
